items.description: Unraveling the complexities of lung cancer through a groundbreaking multi-agent systems framework. Our project leverages machine learning for precision prediction and analysis, offering a novel approach to combat this deadly disease.

items.name: Machine-Learning
items.description: This repository contain the code in which different built in frameworks of python is used to understand the basic concepts of Supervised Machine Learning and how it is implemented using built frameworks of python

items.name: mlops-workload-orchestrator
items.description: The MLOps Workload Orchestrator solution helps you streamline and enforce architecture best practices for machine learning (ML) model productionization. This solution is an extendable framework that provides a standard interface for managing ML pipelines for AWS ML services and third-party services.

items.name: ApraPipes
items.description: A pipeline framework for developing video and image processing application. Supports multiple GPUs and Machine Learning tooklits

items.name: Fake-Social-Media-Profile-Detection
items.description: Fake Social Media Profile Detection  is a machine learning project designed to identify and detect fake social media profiles. Leveraging Django for the web application framework and TensorFlow/Keras for building and training neural networks, this project aims to provide a robust solution for distinguishing genuine profiles from fake ones.

items.name: used-car-price-prediction-crispdm
items.description: Analysis and prediction of used car prices using machine learning models following the CRISP-DM framework.

items.name: sAIfe
items.description: Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning Application and Pipeline Security-Focused Development Framework

items.name: Design-and-Implementation-of-Diabetes-Detection-using-Machine-Learning
items.description: A robust framework was proposed where outlier rejection, filling the missing values, data standardization, K-fold validation, and different Machine Learning (ML) classifiers were used. Finally, to improve the result, weighted ensembling of different ML models also proposed.

items.name: MyPortfolio
items.description: My project involves using SQL, Python libraries and frameworks, as well as working with Machine Learning and NLP

items.name: Machine-Learning-Projects-
items.description: In this repository I will upload my Created Machine Learning Projects Deployed the Algorithms in Django Framework.

items.name: Developing-an-Enhanced-Credit-Scoring-Model-Using-Machine-Learning-Techniques-Achieving-Explainabil
items.description: This project focuses on developing a credit scoring model using advanced machine learning techniques, specifically Random Forest, integrated with the Dalex framework for interpretability. Utilizes the "Default of Credit Card Clients" dataset to predict credit risk while addressing the trade-off between accuracy and explainability.

items.name: fokker-planck
items.description: Implementation of the paper "A Machine Learning Framework for Efficiently Solving Fokker-Planck Equations."

items.description: framework for developing machine (and deep) learning models for structured data
